The collection log is a book that players can receive from The Collector near the stairs in the Varrock Museum's ground floor[UK]1st floor[US]. It records nearly every unique drop the player has obtained from various content in Old School RuneScape. The player does not need to have claimed a collection log for it to start tracking drops.

Drops obtained prior to its release are not recorded for any player, excluding untradeable items (such as pets) provided that they can be tracked by the game; for example, long bones the player had traded to Barlak or buried before the log's release were not added to it, but any long bones in the player's possession were added.

Each entry in the log is tracked by the item itself, not where it was obtained. For example, obtaining a dragon pickaxe from the Chaos Elemental will also log it under other bosses that drop it, such as Callisto and the King Black Dragon.

There is a cap on the amount each item can be tracked, depending on the item in question. For example, Zulrah's scales will only be tracked up to 65,535 and bracelets of ethereum up to 250.

It can be stored in a bookcase within a player-owned house, and can also be accessed from the adventurer's log within a player's Achievement Gallery.

As of an update on 4 May 2022, there are a total of 1,552 slots to fill in the collection log, with a total of 1,395 unique entries being tracked. Pets, gilded equipment, and 3rd age equipment account for 110 of the 152 slots containing duplicate items.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
4 May 2022
(update)

Added the Tarnished Locket and the Lost Bag to the Collection Log. They will retroactively unlock for anyone whos already received them as drops.

12 January 2022
(update)

Nexling now correctly shows up in the Collection log.

17 November 2021
(update)

The Collection Log entry for Penance Gloves will now update on login and when opening the Log.

28 April 2021
(update)

Some new counters have been added to the Collection Log, including the number of Tempoross Reward Permits claimed, and Spoils Of War opened in Soul Wars!

14 April 2021
(update)
  • Brimhaven graceful pieces will now be correctly counted within the Collection Log on log-in.
  • Players can now search for all boss categories in the Collection Log.
7 April 2021
(update)
  • The Collection Log now has a search function.
  • A new counter shows the total number of unique items obtained.
  • Added a toggleable chat/popup notification when a new item has been added to the collection log.
  • The colour of each section of the log changes based on its completed status.
  • Different boss modes now have separate kill counts on their respective interfaces (Dagannoth Kings, Gauntlet, Chambers of Xeric).
  • Gnome Restaurant has a delivery count at the top of its section.
  • Volcanic Mine rewards have been added.
  • Third age and gilded items can now be found in the "Rares" tabs for each clue scroll.
  • A Brimhaven Agility section has been added to the minigames tab.
  • Pirate Hook has been moved from Underwater Agility to the Brimhaven Agility section.
  • Merfolk Trident has been added to the Misc section.
  • Marks of Grace have been added to the Rooftop Agility section.
  • Third age pieces now have their own separate tab.
17 February 2021
(update)

The collection log now tracks Last Man Standing items.

25 July 2019
(update)

Crystal seeds were removed from Zulrah's drop table and subsequently removed from its section within the collection log. Drops from The Gauntlet, Zalcano, Prifddinas were added to the collection log.

4 July 2019
(update)

Drops from Sarachnis were added to the collection log.

25 April 2019
(update)

The Spiked manacles and Climbing boots (g) entries were switched around.

7 February 2019
(update)

The collection log now tracks My Notes correctly.

31 January 2019
(update)

Several additions to existing categories were added, as well as four new categories: Rooftop Agility, Creature Creation, Fossil Island Notes and My Notes.

13 December 2018
(update)

Several additions to existing categories were added, as well as four new categories: Chompy bird hats and Random event rewards.

10 December 2018

The collection log was made available to free-to-play players.
